From the conception of the brand to its transfer to globalnotoriety, the path was long and was marked by many turning points. But above all, the brand has found within it its raison d’être: to encourage responsible behavior among consumers of a society addicted to waste.

We had the chance to meet Jean-Marc Lobkondou Tchandja, the creator and Director of Conscious Recycling :

In a few words, can you summarize your career path?

From Bénin to Paris more than 30 years ago , I chose to start sciences before becoming involved in the eco-neighborhood. I continued my academic journey and obtained an advanced degree in Economic Science at the University of Lille in 2008. It was then that I was propelled into a legal work environment where at the bottom of my heart I had not expected to go. I remained at the forefront of this exciting career for a year before setting on a new project to diversify my horizons.
